## Actions Taken:
- ✅ Fixed lodash prototype pollution vulnerability (4.17.21 → 4.17.23)
- ✅ Fixed Vite `server.fs.deny` bypass + arbitrary file read via WebSocket (7.3.1 → 7.3.2)
  - CVE: GHSA-vg6x-rcgg-rjx6 (fs.deny bypassed with queries)
  - CVE: GHSA-4fhq-7fr5-qj7c (arbitrary file read via dev server WebSocket)
- ✅ esbuild upgraded transitively to 0.27.4 (via vite@7.3.2), resolving GHSA-67mh-4wv8-2f99
- ✅ Verified production bundle has 0 vulnerabilities

## Monitoring Plan:
- Run `npm audit` monthly
- Monitor vite release notes for breaking changes in v8.x
- Check for new security advisories on direct dependencies

## Development Security Best Practices:
- Don't run dev server on public/untrusted networks
- Use localhost binding only for dev server
- Don't expose dev server ports externally
- Keep development environment isolated

